SALMONELLOSIS - IRELAND: BACKGROUND
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Salmonella typhimurium DT104, ham - Ireland: recall 20000229202525
Date: Wed, 01 Mar 2000 06:25:52 +0200
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background information on salmonellosis in Ireland was
extracted from GIDEON <http://www.cyinfo.com>
Year Number of salmonellosis cases reported
1982 175
1983 205
1984 287
1985 152
1986 265
1987 249
1988 271
1989 427
1990 473
1991 484
1992 270
1993 295
1994 338
1995 571
1996 678
1997 959
1998 1257
- Three outbreaks of _Salmonella enteritidis_ infection were ascribed to
eggs during June to July 1997.
- Four outbreaks (25 cases) of _S. enteritidis_ infection were ascribed to
eggs during June to July 1998.
- An outbreak (110 cases - 35 hospitalized) of _S. enteritidis_ PT-4
infection was traced to eggs served at at Chinese restaurant in Dublin in
1999.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
